  <div class="section">
    <h2>üìö Glossary of Key Terms</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Hover any dotted‚Äëunderline term anywhere on the page for a quick definition.</p>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Term</th>
          <th>Definition</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>NRR (Net Revenue Retention)</td><td>Revenue retained from existing customers over time, including upgrades, downgrades, and churn.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>GRR (Gross Revenue Retention)</td><td>Revenue retained from existing customers, excluding expansions but including downgrades and churn.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Churn</td><td>The percentage of customers or revenue lost in a given time period.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>TTV (Time to Value)</td><td>The time it takes for a customer to get value from the product after purchase.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>CSM</td><td>Customer Success Manager ‚Äì responsible for ensuring customer outcomes and satisfaction post-sale.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>MAU / MAD</td><td>Monthly Active Users / Developers ‚Äì measures engagement with the platform.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>QBR (Quarterly Business Review)</td><td>A structured meeting between vendor and customer to review progress, outcomes, and next steps.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>ICP (Ideal Customer Profile)</td><td>The profile of customers most likely to benefit from and succeed with your product.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Executive Sponsor</td><td>A high-level internal stakeholder who supports the product internally and helps with strategic alignment.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Advocacy</td><td>Customer actions that promote your brand‚Äîtestimonials, referrals, speaking engagements, etc.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Onboarding</td><td>Initial phase after purchase where customers are trained and guided to first value.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Activation</td><td>The point at which a user begins to use core features of the product effectively.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Engagement</td><td>Ongoing use and interaction with the product over time.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Adoption</td><td>Depth and breadth of usage across users and teams within a customer organization.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Expansion</td><td>Growth in product usage via new users, features, or departments.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Health Score</td><td>A composite metric indicating customer satisfaction and risk using activity, usage, support, etc.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Product Stickiness</td><td>A measure of how often and deeply users return to the product.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Playbook</td><td>A standardized set of actions or workflows to be followed in specific customer scenarios.</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
 
